$$ \ln c = {(r - {r_0})^2}{/}4Dt + \ln {c_0} $$
\end{document}gave the critical concentration (from the y-intercept) of 55.46 μM in terms of Cu atoms, which is close to the minimum inhibitory concentration of 40 μM determined by the MIC assay. This MIC value is lower than the Stachybotrys chartarum MIC values reported for carneic acid (75 μM, 25 μg/mL), penicillin G (299 μM, 100 μg/mL), or itraconazole (142 μM–142 mM; 0.1–100 mg/mL) but higher than the 2.5 μM (3.12 μg/mL) [43] for actinomycin D (which, however, is highly toxic) [21].
